Program: Last Word
Title: Trevor Bailey, Ernest McCulloch, John Paul Getty III, Gary Moore
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00y9tbz
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 13 Feb 2011
On Last Word with John Wilson this week: Test Match star Trevor Bailey is remembered, both at the crease and in the commentary box, by his friend Henry Blofeld. Dr Ernest McCulloch pioneered stem-cell research which led to the first bone-marrow transplants. John Paul Getty III lost his ear to kidnappers, was snubbed by his billionaire grandfather and suffered a crippling stroke. We hear the story of massive wealth and family tragedy. And rock star Greg Lake tells us how, when he was putting together a new band, blues guitarist Gary Moore passed the audition simply by 'tuning up'. Show less